message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. Pasteurella multocida is the most common cause of infection from dog bites, with a 50-60% incidence rate. Pseudomonas aeruginosa is commonly found in soil and water, and can cause infection in burns or wounds in hospitalized patients. Clostridium tetani is a bacteria that causes tetanus, but is rare in dog bites. Fusobacterium is a bacteria commonly found in dental infections, but is not as commonly associated with animal bites.
